    Namespace Name Admin Only Log Summary Generates Event Version Added     email editconfig yes yes yes 1 (Removed in 1.2)    This API namespace was depricated in version 1.1, and removed in version 1.2. Please look at the alertplugins/* API namespace for the repacement for this functionality.
 Description Configure SSMTP
Input Arguments  Required:  &ldquo;rootaddress&rdquo; (String) &ldquo;mailserver&rdquo; (String) &ldquo;port&rdquo; (String) &ldquo;security&rdquo; (String) (&ldquo;TLS&rdquo; or &ldquo;STARTTLS&rdquo; or &ldquo;TLS+STARTTLS&rdquo;) &ldquo;AuthUser&rdquo; (String) &ldquo;AuthPass&rdquo; (String) &ldquo;AuthMethod&rdquo; (String)   Configuration of SSMTP { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;writeconfig&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;rootaddress&quot; : &quot;email@domain.com&quot;, &quot;mailserver&quot; : &quot;smtp.domain.com&quot;, &quot;port&quot; : &quot;587&quot;, &quot;security&quot; &quot;TLS+STARTTLS&quot;, &quot;AuthUser&quot; &quot;useraddress&quot;, &quot;AuthPass&quot; &quot;userpass&quot;, &quot;AuthMethod&quot; : &quot;LOGIN&quot; } }  Reply Example { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;response&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;result&quot; : &quot;success&quot; } }

    Namespace Name Admin Only Log Summary Generates Event Version Added     email send_test Yes No No 1 (Removed in 1.2)    This API namespace was depricated in version 1.1, and removed in version 1.2. Please look at the alertplugins/* API namespace for the repacement for this functionality.
 Description Send a test email to a designated address. This can be used for verifying that the system email configuration is setup properly and functional.
Input Arguments  Required:  &ldquo;to&rdquo; (String) or (JsonArray) : Email address(es) to send the test email to.   Request Example Arguments for single recipiant { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;send_test&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;to&quot; : &quot;address_1@domain.com&quot; } }  Request Example Arguments for multiple recipiants { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;send_test&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;to&quot; : [&quot;address_1@domain.com&quot; , &quot;address_2@domain.com&quot;] } }  Reply Example { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;response&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;result&quot; : &quot;success&quot; } }

    Namespace Name Admin Only Log Summary Generates Event Version Added     email writeconfig yes yes yes 1 (Removed in 1.2)    This API namespace was depricated in version 1.1, and removed in version 1.2. Please look at the alertplugins/* API namespace for the repacement for this functionality.
 Description Write SSMTP Configuration
Input Arguments  Required:  &ldquo;rootaddress&rdquo; (String) : This email address will appear in the &ldquo;From&rdquo; field of email alerts &ldquo;mailserver&rdquo; (String) : Address to contact for email submissions (Example: &ldquo;smtp.gmail.com&rdquo;) &ldquo;port&rdquo; (String) : Port number to use when contacting the mail server (Example: &ldquo;587&rdquo;); &ldquo;security&rdquo; (String) (&ldquo;TLS&rdquo; or &ldquo;STARTTLS&rdquo; or &ldquo;TLS+STARTTLS&rdquo;) &ldquo;AuthUser&rdquo; (String) : Username to use when connecting to the mailserver &ldquo;AuthPass&rdquo; (String) : Password to use when connecting to the mailserver &ldquo;AuthMethod&rdquo; (String) : Type of authentication to mailserver (&ldquo;LOGIN&rdquo; is standard username/password).   Request Example Arguments { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;writeconfig&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;rootaddress&quot; : &quot;email@domain.com&quot;, &quot;mailserver&quot; : &quot;smtp.domain.com&quot;, &quot;port&quot; : &quot;587&quot;, &quot;security&quot; &quot;TLS+STARTTLS&quot;, &quot;AuthUser&quot; &quot;useraddress&quot;, &quot;AuthPass&quot; &quot;userpass&quot;, &quot;AuthMethod&quot; : &quot;LOGIN&quot; } }  Reply Example { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;email&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;response&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;some_id&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : { &quot;result&quot; : &quot;success&quot; } }
